:32-] &nbsp; %0a>>%3c%3c%0a!!!!!jess_smith%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0a'''Variation among Languages'''%0a>>messageitem%3c%3c%0aBesides geography causing different languages and changes within those languages, I think important factors are culture and history. Some places can be incredibly close together, but because of a completely different history the language used there can be extremely different from a neighboring place. The reason why different languages use such different ways communicate using their mouths could also stem from history, perhaps just from different ancient languages. As they evolved into modern day languages, they probably stuck with the same mouth motions but changed other aspects of the language. %0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210202-223235-911620#%0a%0a%0a%0a(:Section: :)%0a(:Category: PracticeCategory:)
